.container-fluid(ng-controller='consoleCtrl')
  ol.breadcrumb
    li
      a Developers
    li.active Console
  .container-fluid
    div.m-t-60.text-center(ng-hide='current')
      h4.c-gray Please choose an API to start
    div(ng-show='current')
      .row
        .col-sm-6
          .card
            .card-header.m-b-20
              h2.normal
                | {{current.url}}
                small {{current.summary}}
              button.btn.btn-float.bgm-blue.waves-effect(ng-click="submit()" ng-show="current.enabled")
                i.zmdi.zmdi-mail-send
            .card-body.card-padding.p-t-5
              p.alert.alert-info(ng-show="current.type=='get_bookings'") This API is not available yet.
              div(ng-show="current.type=='post_bookings'")
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.entity_id" placeholder='* entity_id')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      span.c-red [required]
                      |  The object id in your PMS. This can be your reservation record id or any record which has reservation information or check-in and check-out information if reservation is not available. Our GMS uses this
                      span.c-blue  entity_id
                      |  in combination with
                      span.c-blue  entity_type
                      |  to create a unique document for your object. Next time you send same
                      span.c-blue  entity_id
                      |  and
                      span.c-blue  entity_type
                      |  , Tipi check for existance of the document and update it.
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.entity_type" placeholder='* entity_type')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      span.c-red [required]
                      |  This is your record type or class name. It's recommended to have underscored lower case name.
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.name" placeholder='name')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Name of person who has done the booking or check-in.
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.email" placeholder='email')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Email address of booking or check-in.
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.from" placeholder="from")
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Start date of booking in
                      span.c-blue  "ISO 8601"
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.to" placeholder="to")
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | End date of booking in
                      span.c-blue  "ISO 8601"
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.reference_number" placeholder="reference_number")
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Reference number of booking which is generated by booking website.
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.source" placeholder="source")
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Name of booking website without subdomain. e.g. www.booking.com should be sent as 
                      span.c-blue booking.com
                      | .
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.price" placeholder="price")
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Total price of booking.
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.guests_count" placeholder='guests_count')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Total number of guests listed in this booking.
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.check_in_at" placeholder='check_in_at')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Check-in time in
                      span.c-blue "ISO 8601"
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.check_out_at" placeholder='check_out_at')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Check-out time in
                      span.c-blue "ISO 8601"
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.city" placeholder='city')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | City of the person
                .row.m-b-5
                  .col-md-6
                    .fg-line
                      input.form-control.input-sm(type='text' ng-model="request.country" placeholder='country')
                  .col-md-6
                    p.c-gray
                      | Country of the person
        .col-sm-6
          .card
            .card-header
              h2 Response
            .card-body.card-padding
              div(ng-show="current.type=='get_bookings'")
              pre(pretty-json='response')
          .card
            .card-header
              h2 Description
            .card-body.card-padding
              div(ng-show="current.type=='post_bookings'")
                p This will create a reservation document or account document as long as both entity_id and entity_type are provided.
                p If there is a document in GMS with same entity_id and entity_type, it is an update request otherwise it is a create request.
                h4 Usage
                ul
                  li It can be called at reservation time
                  li Whenever reservation is updated with more information
                  li On check-in or check-out to inform the GMS with extra information including check-in, check-out time
